  <li>2. Copy the public key to the WSL machine e.g. using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">croc</code> <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">croc ~/.ssh/wsl2.pub</code></li>
  <li>3. Rename the nologin file to allow logins to WSL: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo mv /var/run/nologin /var/run/2023-01-31-renamed-nologin</code> &lt;â€“ Otherwise ssh will fail (it will be stuck on <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Starting shell...</code> )</li>
  <li>4. start ngrok <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ngrok tcp 22</code></li>
